1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 32-12.2-04 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to notice requirements for claims against the state.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 32-12.2-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 32-12.2-04. Notice required - Payment of claims.
7 1. a. A person bringing a claim against the state or a state employee for an injury shall
8 present to the director of the office of management and budget within one
9 hundred eighty days after the alleged injury is discovered or reasonably should
10 have been discovered a written notice of the alleged claim stating the time, place,
11 and circumstances of the injuryclaim, the names of any state employees known
12 to be involved, and the amount of compensation or other relief demanded.
13 b. If the claim is one for serious injury, notice must be presented to the director of
14 the office of management and budget within one year after the alleged serious
15 injury is discovered or reasonably should have been discovered. For purposes of
16 this section, "serious injury" has the meaning as provided in section 26.1 - 41 - 01 .
17 c. The time for giving the notice does not include the time during which a person
18 injured is incapacitated by the injury from giving the notice. If the claim is one for
19 death, the notice may be presented by the personal representative, surviving
20 spouse, or next of kin within one year after the alleged injury resulting in the
21 death.
22 c. d . The time for giving the notice is waived for a claim for relief that resulted from
23 sexual assault, sexual abuse, gross sexual imposition, or any other claim based
24 on a sexual act or sexual contact as defined in chapter 12.1-20.
